        <item>
                <title>Drush</title>
                <description>
&lt;p&gt;Drush is the best tool for Drupal development and administration. I liked it since the firt time I used it. I consider it an essential tool for Drupal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Downloading and enabling a module is as simple as typing “drush en -y module_name”.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;d en -y url
url was not found.                                                     &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;warning&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
The following projects provide some or all of the extensions not found:     &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;ok&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
url
Would you like to download them? &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;y/n&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;: y
Project url &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;7.x-1.0&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; downloaded to sites/all/modules/contrib/url.     &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;success&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
The following extensions will be enabled: url
Do you really want to &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;? &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;y/n&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;: y
url was enabled successfully.&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

