        <item>
                <title>Start off</title>
                <description>
&lt;h2 id=&quot;starting-off&quot;&gt;Starting off&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I decided to create my personal website using &lt;a href=&quot;http://jekyllrb.com/&quot;&gt;Jekyll&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://getbootstrap.com/&quot;&gt;Bootstrap&lt;/a&gt;. I usually enjoy Wordpress but I always want to try more!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It’s really easy and simple. I followed the tutorial at &lt;a href=&quot;http://jekyllbootstrap.com/&quot;&gt;JekyllBootstrap.com&lt;/a&gt;. There are useful information and everything you need to know to get started. Check it out!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;git clone https://github.com/plusjade/jekyll-bootstrap.git miguelos.github.io
&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd &lt;/span&gt;miguelos.github.com
&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;git remote &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt;-url origin git@github.com:miguelos/miguelos.github.io.git
&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;git push origin master&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now starts the best part: Geting into the development and customization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;jekyll serve --watch&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The switch ‘–watch’ auto-generates the website every time a file changes.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You’ll get your new jekyll static page runing on local. Take a look at http://localhost:4000. Easy and fun!&lt;/p&gt;

